5. Where to Use?
Callbacks (map, filter, reduce)

Event listeners (when you donâ€™t need dynamic this)

Short inline functions

const numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4];
const squares = numbers.map(n => n * n);
console.log(squares); // [1, 4, 9, 16]

âœ… Summary:

Before ES6 â†’ used function keyword for everything.

After ES6 â†’ can use arrow functions for concise syntax & lexical this.
